{"title":"The tourist culture that is Copenhagen","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/900934466/0/marginalrevolution~The-tourist-culture-that-is-Copenhagen.html","date":1720595445000,"content":"<blockquote>\r\n<p>A new fee for Venice day trippers. A looming <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.bbc.com/travel/article/20240701-what-does-a-world-without-airbnb-look-like\" target=\"_blank\">ban</a> on vacation rentals in Barcelona. Restrictions on the sale of alcohol in Majorca. At a time when overwhelmed European destinations are slapping tourists with restrictions and fees, Copenhagen is trying a different approach: rewarding visitors who act responsibly.</p>\r\n<p>Beginning July 15, tourists who demonstrate <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.visitcopenhagen.com/copenpay\" target=\"_blank\">climate-friendly travel behavior</a> by participating in the city’s green initiatives — including cycling, train travel and clean-up efforts — will be granted access to museum tours, kayak rentals, free meals and more.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/08/travel/copenhagen-sustainable-tourism.html\" target=\"_blank\">more</a> from <span> </span><span><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nytimes.com/by/ceylan-yeginsu\">Ceylan Yeğinsu</a></span> at the NYT.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/07/the-tourist-culture-that-is-copenhagen.html\">The tourist culture that is Copenhagen</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/900934466/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://fee